{"itemid":551,"subject":"British Fantasy Awards","event":"The British Fantasy Society has released its Long List of nominees for its 2010 awards.\r\n \r\nIt is a very long list, mind you, but I am pleased to say that SONGS OF THE DYING EARTH is among the nominees for Best Anthology, and three of the stories therein have been nominated as well -- Matthew Hughes and Walter Jon Williams in Best Novella, and Robert Silverberg in Best Short Story.  (There is no \"novelette\" category in the BSFS awards.  Not sure what the word limits are). \r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://pics.livejournal.com/grrm/pic/0006x74a/\"><img src=\"http://pics.livejournal.com/grrm/pic/0006x74a/s320x240\" width=\"151\" height=\"240\" border='0'/></a>\r\n\r\nThe full list can be seen at:\r\n \r\nhttp://www.britishfantasysociety.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=592&Itemid=35\r\n\r\nCongratulations to Matthew, Walter, and Bob.\r\n\r\nThe next step for the BSFS is to whittle this Long List down to five finalists in each category for the Short List.","ditemid":141272,"eventtime":"2010-03-21 14:10:00","props":{"current_moodid":109,"commentalter":1269309776,"opt_lockcomments":1,"personifi_word_count":137,"opt_screening":"F","interface":"web","revnum":1,"personifi_tags":"17:3,18:11,6:3,8:3,10:3,23:3,1:3,16:3,3:77,4:55,20:3,9:3,21:11,22:3","revtime":1269381427},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2010-03-21 20:10:19","anum":216,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html","event_timestamp":1269180600,"reply_count":9,"comments":[{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/51443191/3030116","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242072#t9242072","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242072#t9242072","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242072#t9242072","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"hippoiathanatoi","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":9242072,"talkid":36101,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242072#t9242072","upictitle":"Elio &amp; Linda: Elio","article":"A very long list, indeed, but I've a good feeling about the chances for an anthology shortlisting. Good luck to you, Gardner, and the others. :)<br /><br />As to the rest of it, I admit, I blinked a moment when seeing <em>Skin Trade</em> in the Best Novel longlist, and wondered how I missed an expanded version of \"The Skin Trade\" getting published.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","ctime":"March 21 2010, 21:29:40 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"hippoiathanatoi","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"hippoiathanatoi","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"hippoiathanatoi","ctime_ts":1269206980,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/70502886/10865290","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242328#t9242328","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242328#t9242328","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242328#t9242328","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"philmophlegm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://philmophlegm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":9242328,"talkid":36102,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242328#t9242328","upictitle":"philmophlegm: Sid James","article":"I need to get around to writing an LJ review of SotDE sometime. The short version is \"I loved it\", but there should be a longer version where I review each tale in turn. Actually I loved it so much that last night I bought twelve Vance novels second hand. I'm a big Dying Earth fan, and liked Lyonesse and loved Emphyrio, but that still leaves Durdane, Demon Princes and of course Planet of Adventure. That last series being particularly memorable to British readers for having a second volume entitled \"Servants of the Wankh\"...","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","ctime":"March 21 2010, 21:55:55 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://philmophlegm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"philmophlegm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"philmophlegm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://philmophlegm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"philmophlegm","ctime_ts":1269208555,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/117094227/2289645","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242584#t9242584","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242584#t9242584","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=9242584#t9242584","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"jere7my","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://jere7my.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":9242584,"talkid":36103,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/141272.html?thread=92